     1	//! Dev-loop perf gates (0.7.2 PR-6).
     2	//!
     3	//! A fast (≤30 s warm, synthetic default) subset of the canonical AC-013 /
     4	//! AC-013b / AC-019 gates. It exercises the SAME production read path
     5	//! (`Engine::search` → FTS5 + two-phase bit-KNN + f32 rerank) at a small
     6	//! N (~1000) via PR-5's [`CorpusFixture`], so developers get a perf + recall
     7	//! signal in seconds rather than the minutes the `AGENT_LONG`-gated canonical
     8	//! gates take.
     9	//!
    10	//! ## Two-tier model (see `dev/design/perf-gates.md`)
    11	//!
    12	//! - **Devloop (this file):** always-runs in `cargo test` — NOT gated behind
    13	//!   `AGENT_LONG`. It is the inner-loop signal.
    14	//! - **Canonical (`perf_gates.rs`):** `AGENT_LONG`-gated ship verdict at the
    15	//!   tiered 10k budget (PR-3 ADR amend).
    16	//!
    17	//! ## Gate disposition (HITL-locked 2026-06-01)
    18	//!
    19	//! Per HITL, **perf signals NOTIFY, structural invariants BLOCK**:
    20	//!
    21	//! - **Structural invariants** (`assert_vec0_row_count_matches_ingest`,
    22	//!   `assert_fts_index_populated`) — **hard assert**. These catch the
    23	//!   batch-collapse regression (`4a95cfd`) directly: a collapsed batch leaves
    24	//!   `vector_default` short of the ingested doc count and the assert RED-fails.
    25	//! - **Soft latency budget** (p50 ≤ 50 ms / p99 ≤ 150 ms at N≈1000, synthetic
    26	//!   path) and the **recall floor** (≥ 0.85, real path) — **notify-only**.
    27	//!   Exceeding them prints a loud `DEVLOOP_PERF_WARN … status=OVER|UNDER` line
    28	//!   but does NOT fail the test (small-N sample noise should not flap the inner
    29	//!   loop; PR-7 owns turning the trend into a CI gate).
    30	//! - **One hard catastrophic latency ceiling** (10× the soft budget:
    31	//!   p50 > 500 ms / p99 > 1500 ms; synthetic path) — **hard assert**. This
    32	//!   catches the projection-scanner throughput regression (`53a270d`), whose
    33	//!   symptom is an orders-of-magnitude p50/p99 inflation that clears the
    34	//!   ceiling while routine noise never does.
    35	//!
    36	//! Both named regressions therefore RED-fail `cargo test` (batch-collapse via
    37	//! the structural assert; catastrophic scanner inflation via the ceiling),
    38	//! while ordinary small-N latency wobble only notifies.
    39	//!
    40	//! ## Embedder
    41	//!
    42	//! Synthetic [`VaryingEmbedder`] is the always-runs default (instant embed, so
    43	//! the measured latency isolates RETRIEVAL — the same reason canonical AC-013
    44	//! uses it). It is the only path bound by the ≤30 s budget, and it carries the
    45	//! LATENCY gates (synthetic recall is report-only — its sparse vectors quantize
    46	//! poorly, ~0.35 @ N≈1000).
    47	//!
    48	//! The real BGE embedder is opt-in via `DEVLOOP_REAL_EMBEDDER=1` AND the
    49	//! `default-embedder` feature; without the feature the fixture SKIPs
    50	//! gracefully. It carries the RECALL gate (0.85 floor WARN) — its dense vectors
    51	//! make ANN-fidelity meaningful. Its latency is report-only. Cold-cache is
    52	//! allowed (the first run warms PR-5's on-disk doc-body cache and is slow); a
    53	//! warm re-run skips re-embedding doc bodies. Held-out QUERY texts are not in
    54	//! the doc-body cache, so the per-test warmup pass embeds them live once
    55	//! (then the in-memory cache serves the measure pass) and the recall
    56	//! ground-truth pass embeds them again via a fresh embedder — so the real
    57	//! path's WALL time is candle-bound and not ≤30 s regardless of the doc cache.
    58	//! It is an occasional end-to-end exercise, not the inner-loop signal. See
    59	//! `dev/design/perf-gates.md`.
    60	
